      <scopecontent id="aspace_906228a32bec9c3f2a0f639859aff728">
         <head>Content Description</head>
         <p>The collection includes 229 lantern slides with photographs and X-rays of patients with orthopedic, musculoskeletal, rheumatic, and neurological conditions before and after treatment. The majority of images depict pediatric patients. Labels on slides may include patient name, age, and condition; physician name; name of hospital; date of image; and slide number. Hospitals named include the Hospital for Joint Diseases, now known as New York University Langone Orthopedic Hospital, and Fordham Hospital, which was the first public hospital in the Bronx, New York.</p>
      </scopecontent>
